                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-9-person128">
                  JAMES 
                  BOND
               <interp inst="t18220703-9-person128" type="surname" value="BOND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-9-person128" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-9-person128" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18220703-9-viclabel41" type="occupation">boot and shoe-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-9-victim127 t18220703-9-viclabel41"></join>, and live in Shoe-lane. On the 27th of May, about half-past eleven o'clock in the morning, I was on <placeName id="t18220703-9-crimeloc42">Holborn-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-9-crimeloc42" type="placeName" value="Holborn-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-9-crimeloc42" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-9-off39 t18220703-9-crimeloc42"></join>, a person said my pocket was picked, I cast my eye off the pavement to the prisoner, and said I suppose that man is running off with it - I pursued him; he was not above twenty yards off; I did not lose sight of him. I overtook him about fifty yards off, and took him to Clinton's. I saw the handkerchief found in his small clothes - he asked what I was going to do with him, saying that he had nothing of mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-9-person129">
                  JOHN 
                  THOMAS GARDNER
               <interp inst="t18220703-9-person129" type="surname" value="THOMAS GARDNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-9-person129" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-9-person129" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an upholsterer, and live in Lamb's Conduit-street. I was on Holborn-hill, and saw the prisoner alone - I saw him take the handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket, and put it either into his side pocket or his breeches. I told the prosecutor - the prisoner crossed over, and he followed him, and secured him without my losing sight of him - I saw it taken out of his breeches.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-9-person130">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CLINTON
               <interp inst="t18220703-9-person130" type="surname" value="CLINTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-9-person130" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-9-person130" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , I am a constable, and live in Fleet-market. The prosecutor brought the prisoner to me - he said,</p>
               <p>"You see I have not got it," and turned his pockets out. I found it in his breeches.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He found my own property in my pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18220703-9-verdict43" type="verdictDescription">
